    "created_at": "2015-06-23T05:02:50Z",
    "updated_at": "2015-06-23T05:02:50Z",
    "body": "API returning an ID usually means the API can be started for infinite times, like `setTimeout` and `setInterval`, since `powerSaveBlocker` can only be started once for each type, current APIs would be quite confusing.\n\nWe can just use APIs like this:\n\n``` js\npowerSaveBlocker.preventAppSuspension();\npowerSaveBlocker.allowAppSuspension();\npowerSaveBlocker.isAppSuspensionPrevented();\n\npowerSaveBlocker.preventDisplaySleep();\npowerSaveBlocker.allowDisplaySleep();\npowerSaveBlocker.isDisplaySleepPrevented();\n```\n\nIt is very simple to use and implement, and there is no complex logic involved.\n"
  },
